result.name: Amore Wanchai restaurant

reviews.text: Chicken adobo looks great
Filipino food choices are great to fill ur craving  of all-time favorite home dishes

Pretty authentic Filipino food, and particularly enjoyed the Lechon, Sisig, and Sinigang baboy. I was really happy that they stayed open a bit longer near midnight just to serve us and were still friendly at that. Good food and good service, can't get any better than that.

This is the place where you come for authentic Filipino cuisine.
You have no idea how popular this place to the Filipino immigrants.. 
From stir fry to stew and even the beer, you'll get genuine authentic taste of "the thousand islands".. they are not serving fancy dishes, just local simple food for soul. I'd say this is THE soul food for Pacific.
Filipino mix with chinese  :)
